##100,000 beds available in Wuhan: Difficult Rectification from home isolation to centralized isolation

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

At the beginning of the city closure in Wuhan, a medical run on the city, the "home quarantine" policy was introduced. But the community resources and capacity do not match, but increase cross-infection within the family. This is the main reason for the explosion of cases in Wuhan since then.

The correction was long overdue, and on February 2nd, 10 days later, "home segregation" became "centralized segregation" . But the initial isolation point medical care capacity is insufficient, also makes the policy implementation tight.

The situation is forbidden. The right direction of policy met insufficient resources, leading to "good things become bad. " Policy Implementation Ossified, slow adjustment, but in the wrong.

It wasn't until the following week that the number of designated hospitals continued to increase, Vulcan Mountain and Thor Mountain were completed, the shelter hospital was launched, and the addition of medical staff from other provinces, that medical resources began to catch up.

Before February 20, Wuhan had 100,000 beds in reserve. 14,000 in critical, 30,000 in mild, 56,000 in intensive care.

The gradual expansion of medical and social resources has made decision-making and policy-making more resource-supported. Learning from the past, the current policy makers pay more attention to the details of the actual effect, more attention to timely adjustment and correction, Wuhan gradually to "fine" patient diversion direction.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 14, the barber was cutting hair for the medical team to reduce the risk of infection from hair exposure. Photo by Wu Jing

For more than 20 days, Zhang Ping (not his real name) , a community secretary in Wuhan, has been recovering mentally and physically, the cough, which had been making him nervous and worried for a time about being infected with the new coronavirus, disappeared: "It looks like it's just a cold. ".

Along with it, the work pressure also gradually lightens. At the end of January, he was confronted several times a day by patients and family members who had broken into the community office to arrange beds and cars, and in the middle of the night he received calls from the community demanding that the body be removed before it was too late for The Adventure of the Resident Patient to die at home. Anxiety and fear were written on his face, and he kept repeating a line that sounded absurd to outsiders: "I have to keep my team alive. "

At that time, the city of Wuhan had been closed for only a week. At the beginning of the siege, a tidal wave of panic, new coronavirus infections and suspected people poured into the hospital, which was overwhelmed by the immediate withdrawal of medical resources. "Home Isolation" decision-making is introduced at this time, in the shortage of resources for extensive patient triage.

Under pressure, more than 2,000 communities across the city have taken on the task of patient isolation and triage. Community workers, like militiamen, are sent to the battlefields of special forces. In the past 20 days, nearly half of Zhang Ping's community workers have quit. More than a dozen people faced more than 2000 families, in the case of inadequate protective equipment, daily home screening isolation effect, arrangement of hospitalization as if it is impossible to complete the task.

As a result of domestic isolation and inadequate protective measures, cases of infection of the whole family are everywhere. The families of the undiagnosed and critically ill can not stay at home, and they have become mobile sources of infection, shuttling between hospitals and communities.

"Home Segregation" can be seen as a desperate act in the early stages of the crisis, but in the apparent failure to achieve results, correction is still long overdue. Between January 23 and February 2, the number of confirmed cases reported in Wuhan increased tenfold, from 495 to 5,142.

February 2, the policy of a sudden change, "centralized isolation and treatment" to the front. However, all kinds of resources did not keep up, the isolation point lack of medical capacity, there is no patients urgently needed testing and access to health care, policy is difficult to implement at the beginning, "due collection" time point has been repeatedly delayed.

With more and more designated hospitals being requisitioned, the completion of the Vulcan Mountain and the Thor Mountain, the opening of more than a dozen shelter hospitals for patients with mild illness, and the increasing number of hotel isolation points for close contact with suspected groups of people, and the addition of medical staff from other provinces became a reality as "patient diversion" under the resource expansion.

On Feb. 8, when Chen Yixin, secretary general of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission and a former party secretary of Wuhan, returned to the city and became deputy head of the Central Guidance Group, Zhang Ping clearly felt that enforcement had suddenly intensified. On Feb. 13, Hubei and Wuhan Changed Their leadership on the same day, with Ying Yong, the former mayor of Shanghai, taking over as party secretary of Hubei Province, and Wang Zhonglin, the former party secretary of Jinan, taking over as party secretary of Wuhan.

On Feb. 15, more than a dozen critically ill patients were hospitalized in Zhang Ping's medium-sized community of more than 2,000 homes and 5,000 residents, finally completing a "zero-load" of confirmed patients. Though half his staff was gone, his work began to focus on the tightly controlled trips of residents to buy groceries, buy medicine, and return to the competence of community workers.

The failed home quarantine

On Jan. 20, Chen Yijun (not his real name) , an Internet worker in Wuhan, was one of the few people to have their homes quarantined in advance. At that time, Wuhan front-line medical staff has been sensitive to the possibility of human-to-human transmission of the new coronavirus, public opinion is still in the "preventable and controllable. ".

Chen Yijun heard his parents eating some cough, immediately separated with public chopsticks to eat. On the 28th, his mother began to have a fever. He told his parents to sleep in separate rooms. On the 29th, parents in separate rooms, three meals delivered to the door, urging them to take their temperature. There was not enough alcohol in the house, and the UV ozone lamp was used to sterilize it in turn. Go to the hospital to do an examination, choose at 10:00 at night, the outside flow of less time, go out to wear clothes and shoes, all on the door concentrated disinfection.

Even so, the infection occurred, and the father's nucleic acid test was positive and getting sicker; the mother's CT showed lung abnormalities, but the nucleic acid test was negative.

Yuan Haitao, director of the Intensive Care Unit at Wuhan Union Medical College East West Lake Hospital, said of home quarantine, it's hard for people to realize whether they are in quarantine and how. Yuan Haitao contracted the disease in mid-january while transferring a critically ill patient. When he returned home that day, he was still warm and sore, so he shut himself in his study. The next day, he had a fever and went straight to the hospital. Not yet confirmed, he let his family do isolation measures, disinfection for the study, in the very professional sense of protection, his family was not infected.

By early February, neither of Chen's parents had been admitted to a hospital, and Chen had seen countless posts online asking for help, growing increasingly desperate and beginning to join the "army of squeezing medical resources" , asking for help finding a hospital bed for my father. He posted on the Internet, reached out to the media, and did everything he could.

Like him, at the end of January and the beginning of February, home quarantine led to a large number of clusters of infected people, but also collectively encountered problems in hospital. The community workers, on the other hand, are the most powerless. Chen Yijun repeatedly called to inform his father of the situation, their reply has only reported the situation.

By February 2, more than 40 hospitals had been requisitioned and more than 10,000 beds had been opened for new patients in Wuhan. At that time, the number of confirmed cases was only 5,124, half the number of beds available.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 10, fixed-point Treatment Hospital-wuhan Eighth Hospital Gate, medical and nursing staff in one by one from the community, sent to the streets of fever or suspected patients. Photo by Wu Jing.

A doctor at the Wuhan Union Hospital Says Hospital admissions have always been greater than beds. At the end of December, when the outbreak began in Wuhan and fever cases began in large numbers, the nucleic acid test kits had not yet been issued, and the standard for admission to major hospitals was CT scan of the lungs. "If the symptoms are serious, they will stop, " Yuan said.

On January 19, the National Health Commission announced the start of the release of nucleic acid test kits. A large number of previously hospitalized patients did not leave the hospital, many cold patients because of fear of care in the hospital, even if the public number of confirmed lower than the number of beds, in fact, all hospitals are already full.

At this point, NUCLEIC ACID test results become the most difficult threshold whether patients hospitalized, those who might have been admitted to the hospital after the CT test, become waiting for nucleic acid test "suspected patient" , can not be admitted to hospital, isolated at home.

Around the Spring Festival in Zhang Ping, two 80 year old men whose CT scans showed lung abnormalities died at home before nucleic acid tests were done. Another woman in her 50s who was diagnosed with the disease was told by the community that her superiors had coordinated a bed for her to be admitted to the Red Cross Hospital on the same day, and that she had been waiting in line for a bed at the Red Cross hospital for a day, but had not yet gotten a bed, her daughter called the community to cry about her mother's death: "She died on the hospital floor with all her pants wet. "

Relatives of high-risk suspected patients also become high-risk close contacts who constantly queue up for first-line admission to hospitals or seek solutions from the community, which can not restrict their access, the sense of isolation at home is gone. Wuhan Qiao Estuary Four community workers, one was infected, resulting in the same office of the four workers were all isolated, the entire community home isolation work paralyzed.

Policy has changed, but resources have not kept pace

The policy turning point came on February 2nd. Zhang Ping and other community workers received a request from the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and control headquarters for centralized treatment of four categories of people involved in new crown pneumonia: confirmed patients as soon as possible to arrange beds; suspected patients for centralized isolation; Patients with fever were concentrated in isolation for observation, while close contacts were concentrated in isolation for observation.

On February 3rd a group of hotels were turned into quarantines, but progress was hard.

The initial request from the headquarters was to complete nucleic acid testing of all suspected cases in Wuhan by February 7 at the latest, with a view to admitting all confirmed patients at 2400 hours on February 5. Later, 9 days before the completion of fever patients test, 924 o'clock before all patients diagnosed with home isolation will be admitted. Later, the timing was delayed..

In the final analysis, the reason is that medical resources have not kept pace, the isolation points lack the capacity to provide medical care, the beds in the designated hospitals are still not available, and some of the The Adventure of the Resident Patient are instead placed in the isolation points. The Article "Wuhan new pneumonia four categories of personnel centralized isolation, why so difficult? " Recorded a patient's complaint: "I am so serious patients drag me here for observation? You'll be on oxygen at night, you'll have nothing, and you'll be dead, won't you?"

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 3, quarantine hotel entrance, suspected patients ask the staff of the current isolation. Photo by Wu Jing.

Zheng Xiu, 23, and Zheng Tao, 19, both living in Tianxing Garden, Jiang'an District, Wuhan, were admitted to a hotel isolation point on Feb. 3 after their parents were diagnosed as new crown patients. Their father went into shock on Feb. 7, quarantine point staff let Zheng Xiu home, she tried to send to the hospital, the hospital was in critical condition, do not accept. She knelt on the ground and begged the doctor to take it, but it was too late. Her father died on February 8. The same day, the mother in quarantine point respiratory failure, sent to Hankou Hospital, the hospital has no beds, only in the hall infusion, their own bags of oxygen. The two brothers sat for two nights in the cold iron chairs in the hall. Eventually, the mother was taken to Vulcan Mountain Hospital as a critically ill patient.

Chen Yijun, whose father was diagnosed and whose mother was highly suspected, went to a hotel isolation point on Feb. 4 at the repeated request of the community, as a close contact group. His original intention was that if he obeyed the community, maybe the community can arrange for a sick father to be admitted. But the community was still at a loss, and eventually he made repeated efforts to find a personal relationship and finally sent his father to the hospital.

On the one hand, it is the support of medical teams from all over the world, on the other hand, it is the construction of new designated hospital and Mount Vulcan and Mount Thor, as well as the large-scale construction of a new type of hospital  Foshan Square hospital.

"Shelter Hospital built late. "

On February 1, Academician Wang Chen, an expert in respiratory and critical care medicine, visited Wuhan and his suggestion became an important turning point in the prevention and treatment of new Crown Disease in Wuhan. In a video interview with Bai Yansong on the evening of February 5, Wang pointed out that the inadequate treatment of patients with mild illness and home isolation will not prevent infection, but will lead to further social and family infections, which is the most important factor exacerbating the epidemic. He proposed the "Shelter Hospital" concept, the use of large-scale sites, centralized treatment of patients with mild illness.

On February 3, the first batch of 15 shelter hospitals with a total bed capacity of more than 10,000 began construction, and they were put into use one after another on February 5. Compared with the beds in designated hospitals, the beds in the shelter hospitals were at first relatively loose, it initially treated patients with a diagnosis, mild illness, no underlying disease, under the age of 65.

Several industry experts said the shelter hospital was built too late. "The new crown is very different from the SARS epidemic in 2003. The number of new crowns is very high, but most of them are mild and require large facilities like the shelter to accommodate patients with mild illness. "

The people who were admitted to the shelter hospital began to dance in the square

Construction of the Tazihu Shelter Hospital, which began on February 4, was taken over by the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine and Western medicine, and the first batch of patients was admitted on February 12. By 5 p.m. on February 13, a total of 430 patients had been admitted.

Ling Ruijie, director of the hospital, told the eight-point health news that in principle, the upper cabin hospital accepts patients with mild cases because the conditions are relatively simple and there are also some patients with relatively serious conditions who are admitted and then transferred to designated hospitals. "there is a requirement that no one [ in a shelter hospital ] should die, that there are no oxygen devices in place for critically ill patients, that there is no safety. According to the Fifth Edition Protocol: Respiratory Distress, respiratory rate (Rr) over 30 times per minute; resting Oxygenation less than 93% ; O2 index less than 300 MMHG; severe case if any of these three criteria are met

Of the 430 admitted on 13 February, 10 critical patients were transferred. "Many designated hospitals are full, can only transfer to their own hospital, other hospitals can not take over, " said Ling Ruijie.

Centralized isolation has kept the epidemic under control, but patients who miss treatment early on need more beds at designated hospitals. In order to expand the critical care beds, in mid-february, the central South Hospital expanded by 200 beds, the government ordered, within two or three days, the admission of critical patients in batches. The hospital overnight construction, will transform the ordinary ward into the Infectious Disease Ward.

But because triage policy is late one step, and the treatment cycle of serious disease patient is longer, fixed-point hospital still a bed is hard to get.

In overburdened designated hospitals, the outside world treats patients as the only requirement for them, but the arrangement of wards in some hospitals is unreasonable, and the risk of nosocomial infection is increased. In mid-february, a provincial medical team assisting a designated hospital in Wuhan found dozens of suspected patients who had not been tested for nucleic acids in three-person rooms. One of the team's doctors questioned whether the suspected patients should be isolated or risk cross-infection. Wuhan that hospital director listened to very dissatisfied, think the medical team is to want to accept fewer patients. In the end, the Beijing medical team insisted that only critically ill patients be admitted to multi-patient wards. "these critically ill patients, the onset of time in early February, the onset of more than 10 days, a long time, missed the best period of early treatment, " the doctor said.

Transitional "homeless patient. "

After Chen's father was hospitalized, he began to worry about his mother at the quarantine point, because the nucleic acid test was negative, and even if the lung CT showed a single lung infection, there was no possibility of admission to a hospital or a shelter hospital for patients with mild illnesses. She was taken to another hotel isolation point not far from Chen Yijun. "only medicine, can not be injected, there is no oxygen machine and other equipment, once the condition worsens, how to do? " This became the most anxious problem during Chen Yijun isolation.

Nucleic acid detection has always been an important index in determining the admission of patients and the number of confirmed patients in new crown disease. First-line clinician is full of controversy to this index however, positive must be diagnosed patient, but because of sampling and other factors, the existence of "false negative" results in nucleic acid detection accuracy of only 30%-40% .

Zhang Xiaochun of Zhongnan Hospital, who was the first to suggest that CT should be taken as the criteria for clinical diagnosis, believes that the virus latency is related to viral load and sampling. After treatment in a positive patient, the virus is partially eliminated, the number of viruses is reduced, it is likely that the sampling site did not detect the virus, the test results are negative, but there is still virus in the Alveoli. In many cases, some patients have multiple negative nucleic acid tests, but the disease continues to deteriorate.

When the nucleic acid test was released at the end of January, the number of confirmed cases exploded, but there were still many negative patients whose CT diagnoses should have been treated and not discharged. In the case of the Fifth Hospital, more than 70 percent of the in-patients tested on January 31 were negative. The hospital issued an internal notice from the higher authorities on February 5. From that day on, "those who can be discharged can be discharged as far as possible, and those who have severe clinical symptoms can continue to be hospitalized for observation or treatment. The list of Double Yin patients will be uploaded later, and each department will try to persuade patients in its own department to be discharged as far as possible. " The notice was confirmed by in-house medical staff and a large number of patients were discharged.

In designated hospitals for critically ill patients such as Tongji, Xiehe and China-South Africa, a tacit understanding was reached among doctors. "Try to discharge only patients with relatively mild illness, many negative patients are really not suitable for discharge, " said a Tongji Hospital doctor.

For this type of patient, decision-making has long been considered. On February 2, Wuhan requisitioned the fourth batch of 17 designated hospitals to treat suspected cases transferred from the first three batches of designated hospitals with negative test results, including the Wuhan Commercial and Vocational Hospital, Wuhan Eighth Hospital and so on.

But the fourth batch of more than 700 beds, can not receive all patients transferred out.

In the Kong Hon district, for example, only the Wuhan Commercial Vocational Hospital was able to receive double negative patients who needed further treatment. The Director of Wuhan Commercial and Vocational Hospital made an introduction to Jianwen at 8:00. The hospital obeyed the arrangement and only accepted such patients transferred from the Red Cross Hospital. They were transported by the 120 emergency ambulance, "double negative, isolated observation, there are basic diseases treated here, such as diabetes, stroke and so on in this patient. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 10,2020, the entrance of Wuhan Business and Vocational Hospital was sealed off. At this time, about 200 patients with new crown and Double Yin still needed to be treated for basic diseases. Photo by Wu Jing.

In Kong Hon, there are also designated hospitals in Hubei Province, such as the integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, the Union Hospital and the Tongji Hospital. There is no designated hospital to receive patients of these types when they are transferred out.

Starting from February 1 and ending around February 10, the business hospital has nearly filled up to 230 beds and is staffed with medical staff from community hospitals and medical aid teams, but it is still "really not enough" .

When nucleic acid testing became the sole criterion for identifying patients, a large number of negative but critical patients, stuck on the nucleic acid test, became "homeless patients" who could not be admitted or had to be discharged.

With a reserve of 100,000 beds, capacity is essential for fine triage

To the surprise of Zhang Xiaochun and other frontline clinicians, the diagnostic criteria of the fifth edition of the diagnostic guidelines were added to clinical judgments of CT images on Feb. 5, which meant that the criteria were broken down in nucleic acid testing.

After a few days of adjustment, the confirmed cases are released to the public in accordance with treatment guidelines. On February 12th there were 13,436 confirmed cases a day in Wuhan -- as if this weren't an actual new case, but a hidden one.

NUCLEIC ACID test of double negative, but CT detection of lung imaging changes in the "homeless patients" have been admitted to the hospital conditions.

To Chen's delight, his mother was finally able to transfer from the isolation point to the shelter hospital.

However, the surge in confirmed patients, more tests the capacity of designated hospitals. In Zhang Ping's neighborhood, the streets demanded that a 65 year old man with a double negative nucleic acid test and a change in his lungs be taken to a Red Cross hospital. The old man became a confirmed patient after the change in testing standards. Previously, because of the double negative test results, the designated hospital did not admit the patient, while the shelter hospital because the patient was 65 years old and did not admit the patient, she became a patient who had nowhere to go but in isolation at home. The street office ensures that the hospital has a bed. But when the patient arrived at the hospital, he waited for hours without a bed, and after hours without food or water or supervision, he began to roll around on the floor. Finally checked in.

Not all communities have been as committed to hospital as Zhang Ping and his team have been. In a community of 1,920 households and about 5,000 people in the Qiaokou District district, all seven confirmed patients in the community on February 12 remained at home and did not go to hospital because of the retirement of a community secretary and the infection of a community member.

The requisition of beds in designated hospitals is still under way, according to Article 25,2020, issued by the Wuhan New Cap Epidemic Prevention and Control Command, "Wuhan will reach 14,000 designated hospital beds by February 20 for the treatment of critically ill patients, " it said, adding that Wuhan is expected to reach a total of 100,000 beds by February 20, in addition to the 14,000 critical patients admitted to designated hospitals, there are 30,000 beds in the light point (shelter) and 56,000 beds in the central isolation point.

In a promising sign, the number of newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia in Wuhan dropped sharply in the three days after it exploded on Feb. 12. On February 13th it fell to 3,910; on February 14th it fell to 1,923; on February 15th it was 1,548; and on February 15th the number of people who have been cured has increased dramatically, wang Hesheng, a member of the party group and Deputy Director of the National Health Commission and a member of the Standing Committee of the Hubei Provincial Committee, said at the Guoxin press conference that the discharge rate from Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital and the Lung Hospital were over 30 percent.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
 Wu Yiting cartography

The first discharge peak will also be reached at the beginning of the establishment of the Shelter Hospital. On the afternoon of February 15, the first batch of 17 patients from the Wuhan Living Room Shelter Hospital will be discharged, li Zhiqiang, vice-president of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University and vice-president of Wuhan Sitting Room Shelter Hospital, told the media: "The last few days should be the first wave of discharge from the shelter hospital. ". Because it's been a week since we opened the hatch on February 7th. After treatment, many patients are in a stable state to recover, and a few days after the objective indicators of the test will reach the discharge standard.

There are many concrete hopes that are emerging one by one. His father died and his mother was in critical condition. Zheng Tao, his sister and sister were admitted to the first hospital two days ago. In the Vulcan Mountain once critically ill mother, yesterday suddenly "want to eat, eat fruit" .

Chen Yijun once critically ill father, February 8 began to accept the Red Xiwei double-blind test, then gradually reduced fever, although blood oxygen has not yet reached the standard, but the most critical moment has passed. Chen Yijun, who had been quarantined at the quarantine point for 12 days, had no fever. He just finished his nucleic acid test, and if it's negative, he'll be out of the quarantine zone in no time. The despair of 10 days ago has begun to fade.
